Description: Pioneering a fully-compliant blockchain economy.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: US compliance is the primary concern shaping the design of the Numeum ecosystem. Where most other blockchain businesses are operating outside the US with refusal to do any business with US residents, Blockchain Assets AI is positioned to serve the high demands of US-regulated markets. Between securities laws, trade restrictions, money transmitter laws, and tax reporting requirements, the barriers to entry are set high, and they will be working closely with regulators to build a better, stronger, faster financial system. Blockchains are distributed digital registries for property. Tokens are digital contracts you own. To bring the old financial world fully in to the digital era, consider tokens a form of ‘electronic security paper’ with anti-counterfeiting measures only made possible through computer cryptography. A user’s ‘private key’ is a digital equivalent to their signature, thumb print and retinal scan, rolled in to a string of numbers and letters that must match exactly in order to transfer any of the user’s property, or to authenticate as the user. The designs of blockchain technologies mathematically enforce these rules.

Full Description: AnywhereYouGo.com is the online community and marketplace that: - Helps application developers speed the development of wireless applications - Helps IT managers speed application deployment - Connects wireless infrastructure providers with target influencers and decision makers around the world. More people will access the Internet via a mobile phone than a PC by the year 2003 according to the IGI Group. This will drive mobile e-commerce, which Strategy Analytics forecasts to total 14 billion transactions in 2005 for a total market of $200 billion. Companies represented include Cisco, IBM, Microsoft, Oracle, Sun, Xerox, Lucent, Nokia, Nortel, Phone.com, Telia, AOL, Bloomberg, Reuters, Yahoo, Bank America, British Airways, Citicorp, SAS, Dresdner Bank, Shell, Unilever, and Daimler Chrysler. The experienced technology staff built large dynamic content and commerce systems while at Eagle River Interactive (now Agency.com) and c2o/EDS. Management team and ownership Lee Wright -- CEO (Dallas), Steve Nix -- CFO (Dallas), and James Pearce -- U.K. Director (London). Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The Distressed Realty Fund I, LLC will purchase for cash two different kinds of distressed real estate at below market prices that will be repaired and rented or earn interest for the fund. The first kind of distressed real estate will be houses, condos, small apartment / commercial buildings. The second kind of distressed real estate will be tax certificates sold by county treasurers on properties when the property owner didn’t pay their property taxes on time. All purchased tax certificates are recorded in the buyers name as the first lien on the property title. Tax certificates are usually redeemed within a 1, 2 or 3 year time period that is set by each state’s laws.    The fund estimates it will pay all investors an approximate 1% income check per quarter which is approximately 4% income per year from received rents, earned interest and net profits. Each March 31st, the fund expects to also pay the investors a fifth income check for their 75% share of all net profits from all sold houses/properties during each business year that ends on December 31. The investment capital from sold houses/properties and redeemed tax certificates will be reinvested into other distressed real estate during the 8 to 10 year operating life of the fund.    The investor can invest their IRA retirement money held in a self directed trust account. The investor can also invest their family trust money, their personal money, and/or their corporate pension money. This offering will raise up to $5,000,000 from accredited investors with a one unit minimum investment amount of $5,000.    The Distressed Realty Fund 2, LLC management office is located at 3960 Howard Hughes Parkway Suite 500 Las Vegas, Nevada 89169. Mr. David Zussman J.D. is the President & CEO of Realty Fund Management 2, Inc. the managing member of the Distressed Realty Fund 2, LLC.
